      "The lunar nodes are not planets but two points of intersection between the Moon's orbit and the ecliptic — the apparent path of the Sun. The North Node and the South Node form a perfectly opposite axis, crossing the birth chart from one point to the other. In psychological and evolutionary astrology, this axis is considered one of the most profound indicators of the soul's trajectory, much more subtle than a simple reading of the Sun or Ascendant.",
      "The South Node represents what is already acquired, integrated, sometimes to the point of exhaustion. It is the familiar territory, the innate talents, the comfortable inherited patterns — whether one understands them as karmic in a reincarnational sense or as ancestral and family imprints. It is the zone where one excels effortlessly, but also where one stagnates when taking refuge in it. The South Node is a gift that becomes a trap if it is merely repeated.",
      "The North Node, at the exact opposite, draws the direction of growth for this life. It is unknown, sometimes uncomfortable terrain that requires developing qualities one does not naturally possess. A North Node in an Air sign for someone whose South Node is in a Water sign, for example, demands learning to take intellectual distance from one's feelings, to communicate rather than retreating into emotional silence.",
      "Evolutionary astrologer Steven Forrest describes the nodal axis as an arrow: the South Node is the fletching that stabilises, the North Node is the tip that shows direction. But one cannot move forward by abandoning one's past — it must be integrated and used as a springboard. The work consists in honouring the talents of the South without resting on them, and in daring the unknown terrain of the North without rejecting who you already are.",
